<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">March Continued 1808</p>
<p>man who I Keep here much against his own will<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sun<sup>y</sup> 14<sup>th</sup> 15<sup>th</sup> 16<sup>th</sup> 17<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Cadien put 56 large Kettles full of water in the Ice House<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday 20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Three young men arrived from Capot Rouge's &amp; Levriers band, they brought 8 Skins of Fresh meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Slept 4 nights coming to the Fort<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave them bits of Tobacco &amp; Drams, Paid &amp; Sent them off &#8211; with instructions to their <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Moguls</span> not to come to the Fort but after the departure of the Ice &#8211; &amp; that they should remove a little farther from the Fort in quest of Beaver<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent them according to request 1 Fm Tobacco &#8211; &amp; 6 meas<sup>s</sup> Am<sup>n</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  This may perhaps be considered as being rather profuse &#8211; and tending to extravagancy<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  But I hope it will also be considered, that I am obliged to do it in order to please the natives, that they may attach themselves to the quarter they are now Steering to &#8211; besides it will also tend to endure others from below to follow<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  When once they will have taken a liking to the Country &amp; then it will be an easy matter for the Clerk who is here (if my Employers should dispose of me elsewhere) to retrench these pe<span class="AddHand-author">r</span>quisites with the greatest facility &#8211; without fearing to discourage the Indians<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fine weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sun<sup>y</sup> 21<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Recieved 100 Hares &amp; 6 Lynx Skins to day from my old Hunter<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent him off again<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Mon<sup>y</sup> 22<sup>nd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  An elderly man with two young lads arrived from the Horn Mountain<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Recieved from them their debts amount<sup>g</sup> to 33 Skins of furrs<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave drams &amp; bits of Tob<sup>o</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>fter this traded 180 Pleus more of Peltries &amp; 10 Hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave out Credits again<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Weather as yesterday<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Tues<sup>y</sup> 23<sup>rd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off the above Indians<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Wednes<sup>y</sup> 24<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My Hunter brought 30 Hares &amp; <span class="DelHand-author">a</span> <span class="AddHand-author">3</span> Pichoux Skin<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 26<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Recieved 45 Hares &amp; 1 Pichoux Skin from my Hare Hang man &#8211; who was also accompanied per an old man</p>

